 Current Appointees)</span><hr size=1> This post is a placeholder which holds the current Knight Champion appointments and program description.<br>
<br>
In it's most basic form, the Knight Champion appointments are simply a designation of four of the top tanks in the guild. These Knights will receive the best equipment and tools available to the KoF in order to increase the guild’s overall effectiveness. They will form the first line of defense for the KoF's raids, maintaining the aggro of the monsters that the pull team has pulled. The better these tanks and their equipment become, the greater the KoF’s quarry can be, resulting in spirally increasing equipment and fun for the whole guild.<br>
<br>
The Marshal of the March ranks the Knight Champions from a list of volunteer warriors, paladins, and shadowknights.<br>
<br>
Eventually there will be other Champion programs to help equip the KoF’s supporting healers, casters, and damage dealers (not necessarily in that order).<br>
<br>
Duties: Your main responsibility is to act as Main, Second, or Crowd Control assist for KoF events. Your character must be willing to die to protect those relying on you and to ensure the integrity of a raid. You have also committed to become as capable as possible in playing your character.<br>
<br>
Equipment allocation and priority will be give to each Knight Champion in order of rank. Tradable items must be recycled back to the guild to trickle down to other deserving Knights.<br>
<br>
Consider yourself an asset of the KoF. This guild is your home, and will provide its resources and experience for your benefit. By volunteering for this program, you have committed to playing at least twice a week in an official event, unless:<br>
1. There is no official guild event that week.<br>
2. The official guild event does not give at least four days notice.<br>
3. Acts of God, real life issues, or server shut down cause you to be unable to play.<br>
<br>
